text:
1st (and 2nd) years:

The Q&A info-session for class bidding starts @11am in W240, after which you can start to finalize your schedule for Winter 2024.  There are some good resources to help you decide what classes to take, like
• the BYU schedule builder (<https://commtech.byu.edu/auth/registrar/schedule-builder/>)
• an excel file I made that is floating around and is partially outdated (make sure to update)
• or the bidding website itself (<https://services.byu.edu/mba>).
If, during the Q&A, you languish due to want of food, please stop by *W122 @11:30am* and hear students talk about the Cougar Strategy Group LDB (CSG) for winter 2024! CSG is sponsoring Chick-fil-A (will have some veggie and GF options) if you come listen to our 20min presentation.

Reasons to attend:
• CSG has LDB options for international students that doesn't effect your visa status.
• We will share information about a new consulting class that teaches "how to consult," which is applicable to all tracks.
• Opportunity to gain actual team leadership experience while in school.
• With combination of CTS (HR) and CSG (Bus. Strat), this is one of the best LDBs to learn about and launch a career into business consulting.
See you at 11:30am in W122 tomorrow!
